header.gameNote: BLUE AND GOLD CLASSIC AT MILWAUKEE WI

article.headline: Winthrop 73, IUPUI 50
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Chris Gaynor and James Shuler scored 12 points each to lead Winthrop to a 73-50 victory over IUPUI Friday in the opening round of Marquette's Blue & Gold Classic. Winthrop (1-0) advances to the championship game Saturday against the winner of the Rice-Marquette game later Friday night. Craig Bradshaw and Michael Jenkins added 11 points each for Winthrop, and Bradshaw had seven rebounds. Brandon Cole led IUPUI with 21 points, while George Hill added 11 points and eight rebounds in the first-ever meeting between the two schools. IUPUI (0-1), which trailed for most of the game, made only 5 of 26 shots from 3-point range and shot just 30.6 percent from the field. The Jaguars cut Winthrop's lead to 37-31 on Hills jumper with 16:40 remaining. But Winthrop went on a 12-3 run to grab a 49-34 lead with 12:34 remaining on Gaynors 3-pointer. Daniels scored four points during the run. IUPUI never got closer than 13 points the rest of the game. Winthrop used a 14-2 run midway through the first half to grab a lead it never relinquished. The Eagles led 34-22 at halftime. Winthrop returns 10 of its top 13 players from last season's team that went 27-6 and won the Big South Conference title. The Eagles advanced to the NCAA tournament but lost a close first-round game to Gonzaga.
